50|$|<b>Helmet</b> <b>covers</b> {{are used}} by most armies and are in the {{camouflage}} pattern of the country/military's camouflage pattern, but some armies do have different covers to the uniform, for example Austrian Bundesheer wear several different <b>helmet</b> <b>covers</b> and have not got one standardized cover for every soldier. The Israeli Defense Forces use a large, floppy helmet cover {{to break up the}} outline of the soldier. The US Army from the late 1950s to the mid-late 1980s used a dual-sided camouflage cover (one side a leafy green, the other a blobby orange) with its steel helmets {{while the rest of the}} uniform was green.|$|E
